n waveguide was also engineered by the means\nof an optimized Si-Ge taper, reducing the coupling losses to only 1 dB per\ncoupler. Besides, an experimental work was carried out to try to shift the\nFranz-Keldysh effect, which is maximum at 1650 nm, to lower wavelength close to\n1.55 {\\mu}m for telecommunication applications.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 19 Jul 2022 14:51:12 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-07-20"}
